13/01/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- The leftist groups Conspiracy Nuclei of Fire and the Terrorist Guerrilla Group on Wednesday (January 13th) claimed responsibility for a bombing Saturday outside the parliament building. 
The explosive device was planted in a garbage bin and caused no injuries. 
In a statement released on the internet, the Conspiracy Nuclei of Fire said that the attack aimed to target "the well-secured temple of democracy". 
The Terrorist Guerrilla Group posted a separate message, taking responsibility for the attack. 
(DPA, ANA-MPA - 13/01/10)
